{
  "text": "When stratified by sample size (Fig. 2) , the analysis showed that trials with small sample size (n<80) demonstrated effective improvement of glycemic control, reducing 0.46 % HbA1c level compared with no treatment [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] . The subgroup analysis of small RCTs showed a greater effect size, partially due to the small sample size effect(the small sample size study with larger variance is more likely to overestimate the effect sizes compared with large trials).",
